'''Volodymyr G. Butkevych''' (Boutkevich) (born August 2, 1946 in Region of [[Vinnytsia]]) is a [[Ukrainians|Ukrainian]] [[scholar]] and [[human rights]] lawyer. From 1996 until 2008 he was the Ukrainian judge at the [[European Court of Human Rights]].<ref>{{cite web | url=http://assembly.coe.int/Main.asp?link=/Documents/WorkingDocs/Doc01/EDOC9130.htm | title=CV at the time of 2001 reappointment to the court | accessdate=2010-12-11 | publisher=Council of Europe}}</ref>
In 1994 he was a head of a provisional committee of the [[Verkhovna Rada]] to settle Crimean issues.
